<item>
            <title>[OWB-828] broken proxies in case of bridge methods</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OWB-828</link>
                <project id="12310844" key="OWB">OpenWebBeans</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;it looks like a concurrency issue with interceptor-proxies since it doesn&apos;t happen in all cases.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;normal ( /working):&lt;br/&gt;
LifecycleInterceptorInvocationContext#proceed L95&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;//reflection calls&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;MyReqScopedBean#postConstruct&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;MyAppScopedBean$OwbNormalScopeProxy0#myMethod&lt;br/&gt;
MyAppScopedBean$OwbInterceptProxy0#myMethod&lt;br/&gt;
MyAppScopedBean#myMethod&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;injection points ok&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;not working:&lt;br/&gt;
LifecycleInterceptorInvocationContext#proceed L95&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;//reflection calls&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;MyReqScopedBean#postConstruct&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;MyAppScopedBean$OwbNormalScopeProxy0#myMethod&lt;br/&gt;
MyAppScopedBean$OwbInterceptProxy0#myMethod&lt;br/&gt;
MyAppScopedBean$OwbInterceptProxy0#myMethod&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;injection points are null&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;there is only one instance of $$OwbInterceptProxy0 for the bean in question, but the final method call gets executed by the proxy itself instead of its proxied instance.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
